    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** offense is primed for a high-output day, headlined by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (75.66) and **Gunnar Henderson** (75.34), who serve as our clear offensive anchors. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against Simeon Woods Richardson, and while he faces a slight platoon disadvantage, his elite xwOBA metrics keep his floor remarkably high. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a top-tier play; despite a moderate opposing xERA, his spot at the top of the order combined with a dynamic platoon advantage against Will Warren makes him a must-start for category production. Additionally, **Josh Lowe** (72.21) provides immense value today, as he faces a targetable Christian Scott (15.44 xERA), allowing **Josh Lowe** to maximize his impact in a favorable right-handed platoon setup.\n\nWe are aggressively exploiting the matchup against Christian Scott, which also elevates **Nolan Schanuel** (64.63) into the utility slot. **Dominic Smith** (55.61) represents our most marginal start, squeezed into the lineup primarily due to the soft matchup against Jose Quintana; however, his score is tempered by a platoon disadvantage. The most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Jung** (60.35), who finished just shy of the cutoff. While **Josh Jung** posted a strong score, the optimizer prioritized the specific stacking advantages provided by **Dominic Smith** and **Heliot Ramos** (60.35) in their respective matchups. Given the scarcity of stolen bases, **Heliot Ramos** stays in the rotation due to the favorable base-stealing environment against Shane McClanahan.\n\nPlease monitor the status of **Drake Baldwin**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Dominic Smith**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Nolan Schanuel** closely. All current scores rely on \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions; should any of these players be moved down in their respective batting orders or scratched entirely, their efficiency scores will shift, necessitating immediate adjustments. We have depth on the bench with players like **Marcell Ozuna** and **Jackson Merrill**, who remain ready should any of the primary starters face a late-scratch scenario or negative weather updates.",
